evidence.title: Milking
evidence.text: milking machines. Teat cups are attached to the cow's teats, and then the cups alternate between vacuum and normal air pressure to extract the milk. The milk is filtered and cooled before being added to a large bulk tank of milk for storage. The average time of milking is 5–7 minutes and a cow can be milked with a machine 2–3 times a day.
